        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 6:41PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 641 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Oconee Springs Park, or
10 miles west of Sparta, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sparta, Mitchell, Hamburg State Park, Shoals, Devereux, Jewell,
Beulah, Warthen, Beall Springs, Linton, Oconee Springs Park,
Rockville, Agricola, Shoulderbone, and Culverton.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
central and east central Georgia.</instruction>
